<subSubSection id="D9F16554FFB3BA1FB4BDF451B1D4FCB7" pageId="15" pageNumber="634" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="915436DFFFB3BA1FB4BDF451B1D4FCB7" blockId="15.[173,1380,744,976]" pageId="15" pageNumber="634">
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFB3BA1FB4BDF451B351FC9C" box="[175,375,817,850]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Eumops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="634" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wilsoni">Eumops wilsoni</taxonomicName>
was recently separated from FE. 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFB3BA1FB720F451B196FC9C" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1843" box="[818,944,817,850]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Fumops" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="15" pageNumber="634" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glaucinus">glaucinus</taxonomicName>
based on genetic data, butit is morphologically indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFB3BA1FB6F4F438B161FCB7" baseAuthorityName="Gundlach" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[742,839,856,889]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Eumops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="634" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferox">E. ferox</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9F16554FFB3BA1FB4BDF41FB18DFC09" pageId="15" pageNumber="634" type="distribution">
<caption id="C5946657FFB3BA1FB4BDF41FB18DFC09" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6418380" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6418380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6418380/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="634" targetBox="[1448,2039,278,692]" targetPageId="15">
<paragraph id="915436DFFFB3BA1FB4BDF41FB18DFC09" blockId="15.[173,1380,744,976]" pageId="15" pageNumber="634">
<emphasis id="A39FEACDFFB3BA1FB4BDF41FB379FC6E" bold="true" box="[175,351,895,928]" pageId="15" pageNumber="634">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from four localities in SW 
<collectingCountry id="E9FC764FFFB3BA1FB794F41FB1DBFC6E" box="[902,1021,895,928]" name="Ecuador" pageId="15" pageNumber="634">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="532FF83DFFB3BA1FB000F41FB6DEFC6E" box="[1042,1272,895,928]" country="Ecuador" name="Guayas" pageId="15" pageNumber="634">Guayas Province</collectingRegion>
including Puna I) and NW 
<collectingCountry id="E9FC764FFFB3BA1FB5C7F4C6B031FC09" box="[469,535,934,967]" name="Peru" pageId="15" pageNumber="634">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="532FF83DFFB3BA1FB63FF4C6B0C7FC09" box="[557,737,934,967]" country="Peru" name="Lambayeque" pageId="15" pageNumber="634">Lambayeque</collectingRegion>
Department).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9F16554FFB3BA1FBC1DF66FBAD2FD7B" pageId="15" pageNumber="634" type="description">
<paragraph id="915436DFFFB3BA1FBC1DF66FBAD2FD7B" blockId="15.[2062,2655,271,693]" pageId="15" pageNumber="634">
<emphasis id="A39FEACDFFB3BA1FBC1DF66FBB17FEE2" bold="true" box="[2063,2353,271,300]" pageId="15" pageNumber="634">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 67-84 mm, tail 45-46 mm, ear 22-24 mm, hindfoot 8-13 mm, forearm 56-60 mm; weight 24-32 g. 
<collectingRegion id="532FF83DFFB3BA1FBD12F6E5BB16FE6C" box="[2304,2352,389,418]" country="South Sudan" name="Lakes" pageId="15" pageNumber="634">See</collectingRegion>
general characteristics of the genus under the Black Bonneted Bat (
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFB3BA1FBCDDF6AFBB98FE3E" baseAuthorityName="Shaw" baseAuthorityYear="1800" box="[2255,2494,463,496]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Eumops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="634" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auripendulus">E. auripendulus</taxonomicName>
). Wilson’s Bonneted Bat has dark brown dorsal fur, and venter is paler, with hairs having whitish bases. Tragus is small, with blunt tip. Chromosomal complement has 2n = 38 and FN = 54.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9F16554FFB3BA1FB1B8F5DBB493FD12" box="[1450,1717,699,732]" pageId="15" pageNumber="634" type="biology_ecology">
